HEADWORD: Chrysanthemum
<hw>Chrys*an"the*mum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/; <grk>chryso`s</grk> gold + <?/ flower.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of composite plants, mostly perennial, and of many species
including the many varieties of garden chrysanthemums (annual and
perennial), and also the feverfew and the oxeye daisy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

